This PDE-constrained optimization problem is solved iteratively, and requires the gradient of the PDE constraint, Eqs. (17-20), with respect to parameters. We adopt classical adjoint-based gradient optimization. This approach involves a single linear solution of the adjoint equation of the original PDE constraint at each iteration, followed by solution of the fields to be inverted: \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
